## Functional tests ŌĆö API layer

Use `WebApplicationFactory<Program>` for full pipeline tests. Override services and configuration at the factory level, not inside individual tests.

```csharp
public class OrdersApiTests : IClassFixture<ApiFactory>
{
    private readonly HttpClient _client;

    public OrdersApiTests(ApiFactory factory)
        => _client = factory.CreateClient();

    [Fact]
    public async Task PostOrder_WithValidPayload_Returns201()
    {
        var response = await _client.PostAsJsonAsync("/orders", new PlaceOrderRequest(...));

        response.StatusCode.Should().Be(HttpStatusCode.Created);
    }
}

public class ApiFactory : WebApplicationFactory<Program>
{
    protected override void ConfigureWebHost(IWebHostBuilder builder)
    {
        builder.ConfigureTestServices(services =>
        {
            // replace real DB with Testcontainer or in-memory stub
        });
    }
}
```

- Use `IClassFixture<T>` for shared setup; use `ICollectionFixture<T>` only when the fixture is shared across multiple test classes
- Do not call `Thread.Sleep` or `Task.Delay` to wait for async side effects; use polling helpers or outbox assertions

---

## Validators

Test validators in isolation; do not route through MediatR for validator-only tests:

```csharp
[Fact]
public void Validate_WhenCustomerIdIsEmpty_ReturnsError()
{
    var validator = new PlaceOrderCommandValidator();
    var result = validator.TestValidate(new PlaceOrderCommand(Guid.Empty, []));

    result.ShouldHaveValidationErrorFor(x => x.CustomerId);
}
```

---

## What not to test

| Pattern | Reason |
|---------|--------|
| EF Core mapping configuration via SQLite | SQLite does not enforce SQL Server constraints or types |
| Framework middleware in unit tests | Test at the functional layer via `WebApplicationFactory` |
| Private methods directly | Test through the public surface; if private logic needs tests, extract it |
| Auto-mapper/projection mapping in isolation | Cover through handler or query tests |
